feat: Complete integration of Windows Composition API with Win2D support
- Added comprehensive documentation for the integration of Windows Composition API and Win2D in `COMPOSITION_API_INTEGRATION_COMPLETE.md`. - Implemented core effects in `CompositionEffectManager` including Gaussian blur, color source, and composite effects. - Enhanced API availability detection methods to check for Composition API, Win2D, DWM backdrop, and Accent Policy support. - Improved user feedback mechanisms to display current API usage in the window title. - Established a robust fallback mechanism for effects based on available APIs. - Added testing and diagnostic tools for Win2D integration. - Updated project configuration to include Win2D NuGet package in `packages.config`. - Created `Win2DIntegrationTest.cpp.disabled` for testing Win2D effects. - Documented existing issues and proposed improvements in `ISSUES_AND_IMPROVEMENTS.md`.
